Tutorial of AWH with FEP pulling

EPJ is a positively charged molecule and needs to
be coupled with an chloride ion to be annihilated.

Step 1: Prepare the system
- modify the PDB file (save as start_fep.pdb) to move one of the chloride ions to the end of the first EPJ molecule
- modify the EPJ1.itp file to add the chloride ion. A flat-bottom restraint is added to keep the chloride ion away from the EPJ.
- modify the topol.top file

Step 2: Prepare the index file
- run through get_binding_site_epj.ipynb

Step 3: Run a test simulation to get the block format of the pmf and set target distribution
- with awh_fep_getinit.mdp file
- mkdir awh_fep
- grompp -f mdp/awh_pore_angle_fep.mdp -o awh_fep/awh_fep.tpr -c start_fep.pdb -r start_fep.pdb -p topol_fep.top -maxwarn 2 -n index_fep.ndx
- cd awh_fep
- gmx mdrun -v -deffnm awh_fep -nsteps 10000 -dhdl dhdl
- gmx awh -f awh_fep.edr -s awh_fep.tpr -more -o awh.xvg
- run through get_init_AWH.ipynb and get awhinit.xvg

Step 4: Create the AWH input file
- with awh_fep.mdp file
- create 8 replicates
- copy awhinit.xvg to **each** of the replicate folders
- add `-awh awhinit.xvg` to mdrun command
